# 2p_combat — client. Walks right (toward where host moves to)
# briefly, then unloads continuous Pulse Rifle fire at the host
# until host dies. After kill, walks LEFT over the corpse to test
# decal visibility and ragdoll position sync.
#
# Pairs with 2p_combat.host.shot. Same shot ticks for direct
# host/client side-by-side visual diff.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/combat_client
network connect 127.0.0.1:24081
name ClientB

# Match host's peer_spawn so my own mech starts where the host
# expects it.
spawn_at 2500 1112

# Aim at host's chest. Pulse Rifle range = 2400, plenty for ~200 px.
aim 2300 1080

# Phase 2 (180-260): walk right briefly to test motion sync of
# the local mech (predicted) AND the remote (host) walking left.
at 180 press right
at 220 release right

# Phase 3 (280-580): full-auto Pulse Rifle on the host. Trooper
# 150 HP / 18 dmg = ~9 hits to drop. Hold fire for ~5 seconds.
at 280 press fire
at 580 release fire

# Phase 4 (600+): walk LEFT over the corpse to expose decals.
at 620 press left
at 720 release left

# Screenshots — same ticks as host.
at 100 shot t100_spawn
at 220 shot t220_walking
at 320 shot t320_trading
at 440 shot t440_dying
at 580 shot t580_dead
at 750 shot t750_aftermath
at 900 end
